   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Aeropuertos Dominicanos Siglo XXI, S.A.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Aeropuertos Dominicanos Siglo XXI, S.A. (Aerodom or the company) operates six airports in the Dominican Republic under a 30-year build-operate-transfer concession agreement. Aerodoms airports served over 3.8 million passengers in 2003 and accounted for an estimated 51% of all air passenger traffic in the Dominican Republic.  The project is to help Aerodom complete infrastructure investments required under the concession agreement. These infrastructure investments include the renovation and expansion of existing terminal buildings, runways, and aircraft parking areas; the construction of new terminals; the installation of new security, baggage handling and other equipment; and the construction of a new airport in Saman&#xE1;.</narrative>
  </description>
